    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="215"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                <head>No. 160.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">West</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 15, 1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With reference to previous correspondence in relation to raids and thefts
                    committed in Montana Territory by Canadian Indians and half-breeds, I have the
                    honor to inform you that I have received through my colleague the Secretary of
                    War the following extract from a report of the Lieutenant-General of the Army,
                    dated the 16th ultimo, viz: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The Canadian Indians and half-breeds who have been for some time
                            trespassing upon our territory have all been driven across the border.
                            None remain on this side of the line.</p>
                        <p>Big Bear, a Cree chief who was for some time south of the Missouri, has
                            also returned to British territory.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
